caption: Beautiful back yard seating with heating. Great indoor seating. There was a wait but the restaurant treated us to free drinks. The food was greattttttt. Breakfast plate and a good amount of eggs, grits, sausage. The chicken sandwich was great, cheese and sweet onion sause on top with good amount of fries. The burger was well done with a side of still juicy. The waitress offered us the many good condiments the resturant offered. Wonderful place. The homemade foccaica and ricotta cheese needed something!!!

Listen, I’m not going to hold anyone up...THIS PLACE IS EPIC!!! My wife, 2yo daughter, and I wanted to have a better burger night than the last. The Farm on Adderley exceeded ALL EXPECTATIONS!!! Tonight was our first time and won’t (in any way shape or form) be the last. -Brandon
Excellent New American food, but even pricier post-pandemic.
The Farm on Adderley, the longest-running farm-to-table restaurant in Ditmas Park
Cannot recommend The Farm on Adderley highly enough. Impeccable and hospitable service. DELICIOUS fare (the beet grilled cheese + fried egg was heavenly!). Beakers for wine?!?!? A+++
I've never had a meal here that wasn't exquisite. Every recipe is unique and inventive!  No heating at the moment but the back yard is fairly well protected.
Amazing customer service. High quality food, dessert , and hot toddy cocktails.  Nice outdoor patio space too. Definitely recommend!!
Great grass fed burgers

I visited a few weeks ago, their antics were cute so why not? But as I walked in I was told I couldn’t because they had no tables in the backyard... as we walked away another of their employees quickly grabbed us and told us it was fine “ come to the yard” and let me tell you ... it wasn’t filled at all for sure there were 6 feet apart from everyone but out of their maybe 10 tables only 3 were filled while walking back there... we were stared at up and down.. we paid no mind... my salad which was almost 30$ had brown lettuce. And the steak my friend got was almost colder then the lettuce on my plate ! My point is.. customer service has got to get better! Just because were Latinos doesn’t mean we’re not going to pay ! It wasn’t nice at all. I’m rating it a high 1 star only because my wine was cold and I love wine. But to be fairly honest they never asked if I wanted to another glass of wine... sorry won’t come again.
Great food, the French toast and egg sandwich was fantastic. The ambience at the backyard was perfect. And the staff so friendly. Definitely going to be back!
Had a lovely brunch here not too long ago. Wonderful outdoor seating too.
Love it specially on summer's nights they have an amazing backyard and food is mostly organic plus a great service 👌
Food was cold and took forever to serve
So about lastnight....thanks to you and your wonderful team. I was able to entertain a pandemic ridden teenager, vegan sister and health conscious mother. Thanks for the mocktails et al.
Terrific cocktails, mushroom vegetable dumpling dish was yummy, great service...nice spot!!!

I used to really like this place...ate there earlier this week and had the most underwhelming and expensive grilled cheese. Cheese wasn’t even fully melted, beets were piled on. Server informed me that it was a little different than what was on the menu when she brought it out because they didn’t have all of the ingredients? Did anyone taste test this before putting it on the menu? Ate inside and it was cold enough to see your breath.

Not impressed to say the least! The food was cold and poorly served! The staff was not attentive! Didn’t feel welcoming at all! there was an Asian man who appeared to be a manger or the owner? , he went around tables several times asking all the white older people If they were ok but not our table! ( Latino males ) no acknowledgment  of any kind from any of the staff! Such an over rated spot!
They have a great backyard.  I wouldn't say they have a lot of food options, but they have great ones.
amazing food and friendly service

I’ve always heard good things about this restarting. It’s definitely one of the staples of Ditmas park area . It has a beautiful set up with a nice backyard. We came during the weekday for breakfast. We had the Nashville Chicken Sandwich with fries. The fried was nice and crispy. The Nashville Chicken Sandwich was perfect! The right texture of the chicken. It was nice and moist but crisp with a crunch to it. The right amount of kick so it’s not overwhelmingly. We had some mimosas which was a nice touch.

Everyone loved what they ordered! Salads, burgers, large plate, and specials. They even accommodated our restricted diet by swapping a vegetable side that we couldn't have. Will definitely be coming back!
Great food, music and atmosphere!

My daughter and friends had a surprise 60th birthday dinner at the Farm on Friday evening.  What a wonderful surprise it was.  The staff were wonderful. The outdoor setup perfect and the food was AMAZING!!  I had such a lovely time.  KUDOS to all.

Awfully slow service. This happened today on September 27, 2020. First off, the host was seating other people before us when they came AFTER us. That’s messed up as hell. I should have left right when I witnessed that, but to make matters even worse.. Once we were by miracle finally seated, we were sitting and waiting for over 20 minutes. No wait staff ever came over to even give us water. We went up to the bartender asking if someone is coming and she said she’ll send someone over. A few minutes later and still no one. What is so difficult to walk over to a table and even give them water? The table next to us who were seated 2 minutes before us weren’t ignored the way we were. I’ll never come back here again since this place likes to pick and choose who to serve. We got up and left. They lost our business today and forever
AWesome interesting food. Salad and cheese plate simple and fantastic. The fried chicken sandwich was awesome, unusual sauce and accompaniments. This place is great
Very good food, quick and friendly service. Definitely a great date spot.
Yummmmmy

A cute local eatery. Good brunch, really friendly staff. I had the crispy chicken sandwich, which was great. The curry mayo is really good, but their hot sauce is amazing. We even asked if they sold it, and apparently we're not the first to ask. I'll be checking back here to see if they start selling it for sure. The service was a little slow, but everything else was nice.
Very nice place, with nice outdoor dining and friendly staff, but wish they had more weekend brunch options.
I loved the garden in the back, and the drinks we're well made. My food was okay, I have to give them props for being creative.
Good place,with good choice of food
Food is good. I would give it a 3.5 out of 5

My boyfriend and I have always been fans of their lunch, we both work in the service industry and it’s nice to have a really good meal before heading off. Pandemic dining is a strange experience, but they do a great job of making you feel welcome and normal. We popped in on one of our days off for lunch and I had one of the best burgers I have ever had there. I usually get a chicken sandwich or a salad, but I was extra hungry. You really can’t go wrong with anything on the menu.
That chicken sandwich is amazing even though they forgot my fried egg.
Delicious food and excellent service.  Lovely garden area in the back.
Nice outdoor seating. Great food! Try the fries with curry mayo.
Great
Relaxing outdoor experience but for the second time I have asked for fries to go with the mayonnaise and arrive home ready to munch. No mayonnaise! So disappointing!
Good food but it should have more options to choose from

I always leave disappointed. The food is always strange in terms of prep or ingredient combination, and I always feel like I wasted money or need another meal because I am still hungry. Just don’t think I can come here anymore. Everyone else seems to love this place though so who knows—maybe it’s just me
The burger is good, the food is delicious and service is fine, but the desert is just OK.

I think they deserved 4 stars for the meal I had but I gave them 5 because there are 1 star reviews on here saying it's "horrible" and "overpriced" - it's definitely not "horrible" and I think the pricing is fair for the quality and compared to other similar restaurants. Anyway, that swayed me to give them an extra star to raise the rating. I'll leave the psychology of that reaction to the professionals and describe my meal. I got a cocktail; the one with tequilla. It was excellent. Cab franc with dinner excellent also. The sunchoke app and the pork belly app were good. Not amazing, but different and good. I got the lamb ragu and it was excellent. 5 stars on that dish. My friend got the steak, I tried it and it was OK. I wouldn't recommend ordering that here; go somewhere else if you want steak. Other friend ordered the burger and normally I wouldn't taste someone else's burger... not the kind of delivery system you share, you know? But she insisted and let me tell you, it's one of the best bites of burger I've ever had. Desserts were so-so, I'd recommend just getting the cheese plate for dessert, that was quite good.

Came here for valentine's day and try their special menu. The cocktail is pretty impressive, well made old fashion. Food is a little greasy, using fresh ingredients. It's tasty in general, might come here for brunch.
Get the crispy chicken sandwich. It's so good. It's made with thigh meat so it's tender and juicy. The fries are good and not greasy. Additionally, the staff was very friendly and accommodating.
Pretty good
Really great atmosphere with quality food
Delicious! And the service was excellent!!
loved it
Great place, great service , friendly employees, delicious food!
One of the best restaurants in this area of Brooklyn
They offer a large range of fresh food. I liked dining here. Staff members are always very friendly, rates are affordable and the spot is always clean.
I liked it
$24 for a 5oz. Glass of wine....Really!!
Good food, friendly environment.

The Farm on Adderley was really good. I had the Beet Noodles and it was absolutely delicious (even better than I'd imagined, being someone that relies a lot on meat for my meals)! Waiting for the food took a bit, but at the end it was worth it. Bonus points for the music playlist, as they were playing Kaytranada and Thundercat 😁

Disappointing experience! I always wanted to come here as i’ve heard good things about it. Finally made it, but was disappointed both with the food and with the prices. $4 for a piece of toast to go with a not very impressive salad? Really? Overpriced and nothing special!
The menu is not extensive, but the options are great. Good wine and cocktails as well.
The egg toast and beer almond cake was the best!
It's a vibe.

It wasn’t bad. It wasn’t amazing either. When I went it was about 60 degrees inside. It’s also very crowded and small so you can’t really expect them to keep the place heated as the front and back doors are constantly opening and closing. My friends liked it but I need to enjoy my food in more comfort than what you get inside a barn.

What happened to my beloved Farm? This used to be my go to in the neighbood for farm to table food. The dishes used to be so good and now they are just mediocre at best. I dont mind paying for quality food and its truly sad to see a neighborhood favorite go downhill like this.

Our son took us for brunch to this place on Saturday morning. The place was packed with people and very loud because everyone tried to talk over the laud music. The menu is very simple and limited. Nothing special to come from another area. We live on sheepshead bay and there are so many restaurants with nice waterview and wide choice of menu.

Great neighborhood spot with solid New American food. My partner and I have enjoyed several dates here. The most recent was particularly memorable. Our server, Emma, was professional and courteous; and with her help and suggestions my partner and I were able to navigate my gluten allergy.  The roasted brussel sprouts were phenomenal, and a personal favorite was the duck liver mousse. My partner enjoyed it with the house made bread, and the chef was kind enough to cut an assortment of crudite for me. We will definitely enjoy many more meals here.
Great service, amazing food.  The Thanksgiving dinner was perfect.

Living in the area over the years, this is my first time coming.  For a Saturday brunch, we got our seat pretty fast as we walk in but I am sure it's just our luck. All the tables are full btw.  Service is very quick. They got you menu and right down to ordering. I think our food and coffee came within 5 minutes. Best part is unlimited coffee and they come around pretty often to fill you up.  My salmon with bread is amazing. I wished I got a hot breakfast but coffee is good enough. For a table of four, we tried three of their dishes and they can be found in the picture.  Price is reasonable. What do I know? I know it's expensive to run a restaurant and $15 for a seat down meal isnt that bad. Brunch for four will set you back about $100.
Smaller menu than expected, but everything selected  was very tasty. Portions on the smaller side but everything was well flavored.  Generally attentive waitstaff.
Nice brunch spot for the area
Delicious!

My family and I came here for Thanksgiving dinner. It’d be inadequate to say the experience was far below our expectations, but here we are. The meal was outrageously overpriced and mediocre at best. Leading up to the evening, I made repeated attempts to confirm our reservation with the reservations staff. Each time, I was given no confirmation and treated with disregard - as if they couldn’t be bothered with my concern over whether my Thanksgiving dinner reservation was happening or not. Customer service doesn’t seem to be a priority of theirs. Had I known this was the experience I was going to have, I would have planned a different Thanksgiving evening for my family and avoided this place altogether. 👎🏽

Not a bad place, but very overpriced. The fries with curry mayo were great, their coffee was horrible, their Crispy Chicken Sandwich was ok too. Good if you're in the area, but I wouldn't go out my way to go there.

Horrible from start to finish!! This place used to be pretty decent but always overpriced. This time was THE last time I will be dining there. We were treated like they didn’t want us there from the beginning and the wait staff was barely audible not did they smile at all-except for one. It was like goth city in there. Aside from that there were only 2 things on the entire menu that were appetizing-the pork mouse and the burger-both were almost inedible. The burger was completely over spiced and over cooked and the pork mouse tasted disgusting with long twigs in it. No one was happy with our meal or are experience and I do not want anyone else to waste they’re precious time or money here. Yuck is all I can say!! Also-things have to be really bad for me to write a bad review!
I like brunch here.
Food was on point, well composed and delish.  Service was friendly and full of care.

Thanks to my friend Gene (a Brooklyn resident) who recommended The Farm... this guide would have had no opportunity to experience one of the best grass feed beef burgers of all time. Who would have ever thought that Brooklyn could make such a culinary contribution? FYI they have an impressive bar and a friendly bartender.
The burgers are on point and the steak was really good. Overall great service except the extra bread my GF ordered never came.
I found the food a bit pricey and overrated. The ambience and service is nice. There are not many options for vegetarians.
Don't know what happened to this place in the last couple years, the food used to be really good but has dropped in quality a ton and has really disappointed me.
Rather small menu some of the dishes are quite interesting and good tasting, However a bit overpriced.

I've been going here for a bit, and each time I go back it gets a bit worse. No more really good complementary bread to start your meal, the fries are noticably less crispy and sometimes cold. The food, which used to be spot on, is now unfortunately hit or miss.
Looks better than it tastes
There burger is great..
Very good food in very fulfilling portions. Try the Burger or the meat of the day. Fried ocra is also a highlight. But the best was the apple crumble dessert. Really delicious!
My breakfast was superb...looking forward to going back!

Nice surprises... we located The Farm easily,  got there early,  had drinks at the bar, moved outside,  and moved inside when it started drizzling.  The staff accommodated our 3 moves no problem,  the food was unique and the bill was reasonable. How could you not be impressed? When I saw "fried okra" on the menu,  I had to order that!  What I expected and what showed up were totally different. But in a good way. It was a nice surprise. No overly greasy breaded fried okra, nope. Slim, tasty okra surrounded by scallions,  a red raspberry looking sauce and cream.  Omg, cream! My wife ordered the edamame toast, and it was delicious. Then the dessert that she ordered was amazing. So yeah, go. Enjoy. And be glad you did!

Like stepping into a a secret garden where the chef makes food that you would imagine eating at a big farm table by rows of olive trees next to a vineyard. To me the food is fresh and elevated classic southern dishes with modern, light flavors. Get there early when they open at 10:30 on Sundays to get a spot in the hidden terrace. You will be happy.

I am not sure what happened to this place. Both, the quality of service and the quality of food went down big time.  We've been here many times in the past and it was always consistently good.  We just went there for the first time in a couple of years and boy was it a huge disappointment.  The staff is super slow and careless, and the menu options became worse as well.  It's truly a shame, used to be a good spot, not the case anymore.
Snooty host ruins experience.  You're working in the service industry--I'm the customer.  Its your honor to serve me, not my honor to be at your restaurant.  Go take a flying F
Excellent environment. Food was delicious. Great wines and service. They also have a rare original Luke Jackson painting!

The Farm on Adderley is a pretty nice place. There is indoor, outdoor (out back), and bar seating. Beers are more expensive than similar places ($9 per draft for standard micro brews) but the mixed drinks are a little more reasonable. They are not the strongest drinks, but not terrible. Food is quite good, and everything was tasty the two times I've been here, but I ordered breakfast foods each time, and it took a long time to come out. Similar experience last time.
Wonderful food and amazing staff. Never had a bad meal here. Highly recommend the Sunday Brunch!!!
Simple egg sandwich with a twist and a little magic. Incredibly delicious!!

Easily my favorite place to eat. Everything is delicious. I always have the trout which is paired with different veggies depending on the season. It's on the expensive side but completely worth it, in my opinion. They also have a generous cheese plate. Oh, and the various saucy concoctions paired with the various dishes are always amazing and completely unlike anything I know how to prepare at home. Jeez, now I am craving their food!
I love this spot! The food is fresh and inventive. Awesome yard!

Still a great place some 10 years since I last ate here. Small plates and desserts are particularly good. (Probably shouldn't have ordered the burger, which came out medium rather than medium rare, but I was starving.) The service is perhaps the true standout, though.

Rough one tonight. I've thought this place was ok in the past. 3 or 4 stars. Tonight  Waited 2 hours for dinner. Several people in our large group had to leave. Food was alright. Not bad, not great. Just fine although some at my table had cold food and some had over cooked burgers. Meh. I'll probably try it again at some point but definitely not with a group and definitely will be ready with a back up plan if it starts down the same track.
Always love The Farm, fresh food, beautiful service. Friendly staff and helpful
This spot is awesome! Affordable rates, considerable portions and the staff members are consistently very welcoming.
Very good use of limited space and excellent food complimented by a great staff.
Good food and atmosphere!
Had a burger. It was yummy
Absolutely delicious!
Spacious and great service! Try the Grits n Eggs!
Great food and service. Quite pricey, especially for Brooklyn.
Great farm to table
this is truly an amazing place. you will enjoy it so much.
This place is fantastic.!! Authentic food, reasonable prices, courteous staff.

Sorry, but for the price you pay at this restaurant, and ALL dining guests have lukewarm food served, unacceptable.   You need heat lamps or just send out dishes individually so patrons can enjoy the meal.  If you go, stay away from the steak.   The best item on the menu was the french fries.

Not a good experience, salad was terrible I couldn't identify the greens, my friend's order was messed up, & the food took too long we ended up taking hers home. French toast was mushy. Waiter had to be reminded to return my credit card. Not going back.
Food was absolutely amazing! I highly reccomend the goat cheese and sweet potato omelet
Amazing place, very tasty brunch. Would recommend to go for Yellow Corn Cakes with beef & Mushroom
Different but amazing food. Friendly knowledgeable staff
First visit. Loved the small and cozy atmosphere. GREAT FOOD AND SERVICE
Its changing,  everytime u I go there now it seems to be a new menu. I like trying new things but then u end up leaving with a bill for $100 and food u didn't like.

When I first wrote my review of the Farm nearly 6 months ago, I was highly impressed. However, after visiting the Farm five more times, and three times in the last two weeks, I'm increasingly disappointed in the service, quality of the food, and what you get for what you pay.  While the food is normally good, it's also extremely overpriced. 14$ for two slices of bread and three small slices of cheese? $12 for a mimosa made with extremely flat sparkling wine and cut with at least 50-70% orange juice? And fries that come out 25 minutes after ordering, cold and soggy? That was just my experience today. And keep in mind, I have fairly low standards as long as I get to eat.  And what about the waitresses who aren't fully trained yet? I try to be a nice consumer, but I've noticed significant price discrepancies when I get my bill. If the online menu lists one price, the paper menu lists another, and the bill lists yet another... that's ridiculous. And of course, the upsurge always runs in the Farm's favor. (I would have fought my last bill, but I had to leave to catch a train). I tipped anyways.  They're also not as vegetarian friendly as they used to be. The chefs/ waitresses also used to be more flexible on making substitutions (swapping meat for veggie entrees). I haven't had much luck in the past few weeks... I wonder if the waitresses are too timid to ask the chefs to whip up stuff off the menu anymore. I'm fairly jaded, and I'm not sure if I'd go back again.  *~*~*~*~ My original review, see below *~*~*~  I went to dinner with a few friends of mine at The Farm on Adderley & the food & atmosphere was excellent. Quiet enough for a lively conversation, but the music isn't too blaring or club-like. Kind waiters. Perfect for a get-together, and it's wheelchair accessible too! (Unlike a lot of restaurants in the neighborhood). And the bartender even had an iPhone charger he let me borrow since my phone had died. 10/10 recommend.  They don't have many vegetarian options on the menu, but the staff is perfectly fine fixing up something "off the menu" to accommodate. Perf!
Excellent as always

This place used to be amazing, but I feel like in past years the quality of the food has decreased. Last time I went there my parents were served spoiled fish. Do not suggest for dinner. Great for breakfast or lunch though.

The food is no longer healthy. Wow new menu updates fails on multiple levels! Have been a customers for over 5 years. I will need to call and speak with a manager or owner explaining my dissapointment with these new changes.  Are they under new ownership or management? The food is no longer as good as it once was.
Service was great, but my sandwich and fries were way overdone. You can see how burned it is.

Spectacular food - going here always feels like an adventure because the food is often so unique, it tastes like nothing you've had before. (which is both confusing and satisfying) Their recent spring dishes with fiddlehead ferns were to die for. Also loved their sunchoke appetizer and pork jowl.
Great brunch service, outdoor seating in the back was not too sunny either - perfect for dining out!

If I could give them no stars I would. We came at the beginning of lunch, 3 other tables that’s it (and they had food already). We placed orders and took an hour for food, one was cold and the other was suppose to be a fava bean salad and ended being a 14 dollar bowl of peas...told them these are definitely not fava beans and they brought it back to the kitchen and no response for 15 more minutes. We asked for it to be taken off the bill and to just have the bill because we need to leave. The server said he didn’t know anything about what had happened, never apologized or tried to correct anything. I have never had a place mess something up and act like nothing happened ever. They were terrible servers and need to do better.

Everything i have ever had here has been amazing.  The farm burger with hand cut fries and curry mayo are not to be missed!  Try the red flannel hash at brunch (or the fishernans eggs if they are available.)
Amazing poached eggs n everything else I had from here. The environment is great quite and so relaxing.

Got a group of 6 people for brunch on Sunday (Father’s Day) the wait was almost 2 hours. Watched many many tables empty out and many people get seated before us. I understand table for 6 is not as easy to sit than for a table of 2 or 3... but I think efforts could’ve been made to combine tables.  The food was mediocre. I got the roasted chicken sandwich and it was fine but nothing stood out worth raving about.  Once seated the service was pretty fast!
Throw back village vibe, great for lunch, vegan friendly.
Way overpriced for what you’re getting. Do not order the trout or the chicken dish if you’re looking for flavor or value.

Ive always loved this place, went recently and I love it the same.  Service is great, back yard is adorable, drinks are solid (I had a blood orange mimosa), and food was great. Kind of expensive, but it was to be expected.
Great food
Pricy. But service is 👍
The food was ok. Your options to drink were water or liquor.  The service was extremely slow though in all fairness they were getting ready for the dinner shift.
Perfection!  Best burger I've had in a long time. Great flavor, fresh, and clean! Good wine list and pleasant staff.
The food here is delicious, I hardly ever say that about american restaurants and this one was delicious.
Multiple items unavailable from the lunch menu, service was sloooooow, seltzer was flat. Burger was ok. Dessert terrible.
Missing items on menu
Delicious with fresh ingredients and new flavors!
The Farm on Adderley, oh my i love this restaurant they have some good breakfast and most of them are low calories!!! This place is a gem
Love the food, so fresh
Very slow service, but great food!

The place is over rated. The experience was as follows, had a reservation, after asking for a waiter, one showed up 15 min in. After notifying that two main ingredients are not available and answering two questions, waiter had to leave for 7-8 more minutes. We realized that getting a waiter again would be hard so we pushed through the order. Also finding out that apple cider was also not available. Drinks started to arrive 45 min after the reservation time and food started getting to the table 1 hour and 10 min in. The menu is not extensive and for anyone with a simple pallet is way too advanced. Options are mostly healthy which is generally good, but for someone not used to it could be a disappointment. Overall food if you like advanced flavors is good and tasty, but was overshadowed by the long wait and disappointed friends and kids. Kids burger was not cooked to order, why did they bother asking how it should be cooked? After asked for the check, it took over 20 minutes to produce one which again showed that there is no concept of time here.  So in all, don’t think I will be back. If you plan to come for a brunch consider your schedule and if you want an experience where a time is not an issue and you want the chef to decide for you what to eat and how it’s cooked, by all means go for it, I am sometimes into that myself, but not when you invite someone less adventurous and also with plans after.
Great burger, terrific wines, lovely spot. I'll be back!

The food was bland and not very tasty.  I had the onion soup. Horrible! The menu does not have much to choose from. They don't give much food for the price they are charging. They served me something that look like chicken soup which cost 22 dollars. They claim that it is a main dish. I've been to restaurants in high priced neighborhoods and received a lot of food for the same price that they are charging. The restaurant is not located in a high priced neighborhood like downtown Brooklyn so why are the prices so high? Also, the service is slow. I took my mom there for mother's day and she told me that it was the worst restaurant that she has ever been to. They ruined my Mother's Day.

Food was absolutely amazing! I highly reccomend the goat cheese and sweet potato omelet. My sister has the farmers breakfast and that was great as well. Dishes are definitely filling. The reason I knocked down a star is due to the wait time. We were told that a table would be ready in 20 minutes and we were sat in 10 so we were happy. We received our drinks right away, but the food took over 30 minutes to arrive. They were very busy as it was 12pm on a Sunday when we arrived, but a 40 minute wait for food is a little ridiculous. Aside from the long wait for our food, the staff was friendly and always kept checking on us, reassuring that the food would come soon. Food was absolutely fantastic but I suggest to go before or after Brunch Rush.

So-so experience... Heard so much about this place and since I live nearby, I wanted to try their food. Maybe it is just me, but I wasn't satisfied with food I got, it didn't taste that good for me. The atmosphere is good, but the service is far from good... Was searching for the waiter and had dirty dishes on my table until I paid the check... 3/5

They told me it was my lucky day that I could be seated without a reservation.  Excuse me, I'm the customer, you should be lucky that I'm coming to dine at your place.  Been here a dozen times, door staff is excruciatingly rude (won't thank customers on their way out).  SUCKS
Delicious but pricey.
Food is good serive "ok"
Very nice atmosphere! Pleasant service, nice food.
Nice atmosphere, tasty cookies, raspberry chai is amazing! Super nice barista.
Good food, good service. Comfortable, relaxing place.

Quite good, with a country ambience and a respectable garden and cocktails menu. Brunch is a winner. I really enjoyed eating at this place. We were immediately greeted as we came in and the server was really nice. Since it was my first time, she gave a few recommendations on what to eat. I ultimately chose the chicken burger (I think there's like an official name on the menu but I don't quite remember). The burger was delicious and was so rich and complex in flavor. It is just not that good. The main reason it is so popular is a severe lack of choices in the area. I'm not happy that I have to change my review to a 1 star experience but that's literally what happened to me when I went to eat at The Farm yesterday.  My friend and I wanted to grab a bite for lunch and I've always had great experiences at The Farm that we chose to go there. We walked in and were seated right away, but our order was only taken way after that, (mind you, they were not busy at all).  Finally, a waitress comes over and takes our order but of course they were out of the one thing on the menu I wanted. I chose a similar sandwich (Monk fish sandwich instead of hake) but asked them to make sure no cheese is added as I'm intolerant.  We waited about 20 minutes before I noticed that my sandwich was sitting on the counter while they were waiting for my friends burger to be ready. Mortifying right? They bring it to our table and of course I mentioned that it's probably cold, I watched it sit on the counter for at minimum 10 minutes. She offered to reheat it albeit it wouldn't taste fresh. I agreed to that but when she came back with my reheated sandwich, guess what?!?!? There was cheese on the sandwich.  Quite comical, I know. At this point I had lost my appetite and was pretty much fed up. I told her to take it back and I wasn't going to order anything else. At least they had the decency not to charge me for it.  At this point, I really do not recommend The Farm for lunch dinner or brunch. Take your money to a place that has stellar service and good food. The Farm definitely lost me as a patron.
